						<h2>New Business Development Manager - Dallas Office</h2>
						<p>Apollo Interactive is a full-service digital centric advertising agency with offices in Dallas and Los Angeles.  We are proudly independent and have been doing digital marketing since 1995 for such prestigious and well-known brands as Jack in the Box, Chuck E. Cheese’s, Wingstop, Curves, Visionworks, and Universal Sports Network, to name a few.  Our services include Web site development, digital advertising, and traditional marketing.  We are excellent at what we do and take tremendous pride in delivering services that positively affect our client’s bottom line.</p>
						<p>We are looking to hire a New Business Development Manager in our Dallas office.</p>
						<ul>Responsibilities include:
							<li>Build a prospecting strategy focused on generating qualified leads</li>
							<li>Engage prospects through various channels</li>
							<li>Present Apollo’s capabilities and experience both in person and virtually</li>
							<li>Determine the validity of the opportunity: relevant marketing need, competitive conflict, revenue expectations, location, etc.</li>
							<li>Collaborate with Management to develop the proper approach for each opportunity</li>
							<li>Be an active participant in crafting the approach, strategy, and solution when responding to RFIs/RFPs as well as other potential projects</li>
							<li>Serve as part of the development pitch team</li>
							<li>Attend local events, advertising meetings, networking functions, etc. to expand your reach</li>
						</ul>
						<ul>Qualifications:
							<li>Excited about the challenge of pursuing and closing business</li>
							<li>3-5 years of new business development experience</li>
							<li>Ad Sales / Digital agency experience a plus but not required</li>
							<li>Self-starter and independent thinker</li>
							<li>Good organizational and time management skills</li>
							<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills, including good grammar, spelling, punctuation and attention to detail</li>
						</ul>
						<ul>Benefits:
