						<p>Apollo Interactive is seeking an organized and team-oriented Account Coordinator to join our Los Angeles (El Segundo) office. This is a full-time position. As an Account Coordinator, you will be part of our Insurance Practice division and assist in our Affiliate Department – managing, tracking and optimizing our company’s new and existing online affiliate database and advertising networks.</p>
						<p>Ideal candidates will be organized, methodical, quick learners, possess great communication and negotiation skills, and have at least one year experience in internet marketing. Applicants must be motivated, professional and have excellent time management skills. Applicant must also be able to work efficiently in a small team environment and manage multiple projects at once. Proficiency in Microsoft Excel is a must as data will be analyzed for information regarding industry trends, optimization of campaigns and scaling of volume to maximize revenue.</p>
						<ul>Responsibilities include:
							<li>Support the lead generation team that services our clients in the insurance industry</li>
							<li>Assist Affiliate Manager in managing and optimizing all affiliate and network accounts</li>
							<li>Contact potential affiliates and networks to join Apollo’s program</li>
							<li>Maintain level of familiarity with all aspects of accounts – including marketing methods</li>
							<li>Manage and optimize campaigns from start to finish</li>
							<li>Build and grow affiliate relationships to provide excellent level of support</li>
							<li>Monitor performance of campaigns and suggest strategies for optimization</li>
							<li>Conduct research on industry and market trends, potential clients, and new networks</li>
							<li>Attend meetings and conferences with current affiliates and networks</li>
						</ul>
						<ul>Qualifications:
							<li>BA/BS degree from 4-year university required</li>
							<li>Online advertising or agency experience is preferred</li>
							<li>Basic understanding of lead generation and the insurance industry is a plus</li>
							<li>Team player with strong collaboration skills.</li>
							<li>Excellent MS Excel skills are required</li>
							<li>Desire to learn and grow!</li>
